@tylermacro10 @Marcomadness2 Sure...We could also look at the amount of market cap added for the entire market though right? Obvi mkt cap to GDP is at an ATH...

That's a fair adjustment. On the other hand, the extreme winners are more contained to one small segment this cycle. Same stat for R3000 was 210 stocks in 2000 and 218 in 2021...only 43 today.

We also run a bubble screen at the index and industry level. No index qualifies currently. Only two industries (semis + construction/engineering) qualify at the industry level. In comparison, 8 separate industries qualified at the 2000 top. Also, seeing multiples contract this year, which is abnormal for a blowoff top/bubble end.

@Marsgains1 Obviously it does not have to track 2000. But, everyone (over)indexes to that case. Not a white paper...just a tweet.

@JoeCarlasare As a wise man once told me, 2 data points are not statistically significant

@SanRT1 @JoeCarlasare Right, his criticism of my analysis the last few months was that it was just based on 3-4 data points.

I'm simply pointing out how I could say the same thing.

In a few months profits will temporarily flow out of TradFi (cool off phase after IPOs).

People will want to know where to put their money because everything already went up so much.

And there Bitcoin will be, ready to begin the next four year cycle.

@Thinker_BTC Time to start DCAing BTC is typically after the June low. Not because that has to be the bottom, but because it likely will be "good enough" if you time horizon is more than a few months.

@Zakqkt @Thinker_BTC true, the low for BTC could be different than for all altcoins

